  "texts": [
    "They devised a novel approach, comprising a convolutional neural network (CNN) and a Transformer-based detection model, which effectively identifies artificially created images from SDMs.",
    "Furthermore, they were the first to assess the generalisation capacity of these detection models across diverse scenarios.",
    "Cazenavette et al. (2024) put forth a technique, designated as \"FakeInversion, \" which employs features derived from open-source pre-trained stable diffusion models to identify synthetic images.",
    "A salient attribute of this technique is its capacity to generalise effectively to high-visual-fidelity invisible generators, even when trained exclusively on low-fidelity images generated by Stable Diffusion.",
    "Dataset limitation The accelerated advancement of image generation techniques based on diffusion models can be attributed to the accessibility of extensive, high-quality datasets."
